  <title translate="true">Class Browser</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Class Browser</text></para>
    </header>
	<para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="Class_Browser_Summary"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Previously, if you were working with the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Dolphin_Community_Edition" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Community Edition</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> from Dolphin Smalltalk X6, the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> was where you would have developed most of your Smalltalk code. On the other hand, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Dolphin_Professional_Edition" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Dolphin Professional</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> users were more likely to adopt the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="System_Browser" styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Browser</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> as their favoured development space. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">However, as its name suggests, it is not just a means of creating code but also a means of browsing the existing source code in your image. Combined with it&apos;s close integration with the other tools, in particular the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Method_Explorer" styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Method Explorer</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, it is a great learning aid.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="ClassBrowserShell.png" scale="61.33%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">A new </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can be opened from the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="System_Folder" styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Folder</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or from the </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Tools/Class Browser </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">menu command in any tool.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> consists of the following panes.</text></para>
